<li id="cite_note-74"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-74">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,3735">"Godhood," Encyclopedia of Mormonism, p. 554,</a> "Those who achieve this state of perfection will become joint-heirs with Christ."</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-75"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-75">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFLDS_Church1997" class="citation">LDS Church (1997), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lds.org/gospellibrary/materials/gospel/Start Here_01.pdf"><i>Gospel Principles</i></a>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salt_Lake_City,_Utah" title="Salt Lake City, Utah" class="mw-redirect">Salt Lake City, Utah</a>: LDS Church</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aulast=LDS+Church&amp;rft.au=LDS+Church&amp;rft.btitle=Gospel+Principles&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lds.org%2Fgospellibrary%2Fmaterials%2Fgospel%2FStart%2520Here_01.pdf&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (listing among the "blessings given to exalted people" that "they will become gods,… and will be able to have spirit children…."); <span id="CITEREFCarter1992" class="citation">Carter, K. Codell (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,3734">"Godhood"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Mcmillan, pp.&#160;553–55, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.au=Carter%2C+K.+Codell&amp;rft.aufirst=K.+Codell&amp;rft.aulast=Carter&amp;rft.btitle=Godhood&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C3734&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=553%E2%80%9355&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Mcmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (p. 553: "all resurrected and perfected mortals become gods"; p. 554: "Latter-day Saints believe that those who become gods will have the opportunity to…add[] further offspring to the eternal family").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-76"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-76">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFPope1992" class="citation">Pope, Margaret McConkie (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,3667">"Exaltation"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Macmillan, p.&#160;479, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.aufirst=Margaret+McConkie&amp;rft.aulast=Pope&amp;rft.au=Pope%2C+Margaret+McConkie&amp;rft.btitle=Exaltation&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C3667&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=479&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> ("All Church ordinances lead to exaltation, and the essential crowning ordinances are the Endowment and the eternal marriage covenant of the temple.").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-77"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-77">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFLDS_Church2006" class="citation">LDS Church (2006), <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_Handbook_of_Instructions" title="Church Handbook of Instructions" class="mw-redirect">Church Handbook of Instructions</a>: Book 1, Stake Presidencies and Bishoprics</i>, Salt Lake City, Utah: LDS Church, p.&#160;80</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aulast=LDS+Church&amp;rft.au=LDS+Church&amp;rft.btitle=Church+Handbook+of+Instructions%3A+Book+1%2C+Stake+Presidencies+and+Bishoprics&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=80&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-78"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-78">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A man may be sealed to more than one wife if his previous wives are either dead or legally divorced from him; a living woman, however, may only be sealed to one husband. See <span id="CITEREFLDS_Church2006" class="citation">LDS Church (2006), <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Church_Handbook_of_Instructions" title="Church Handbook of Instructions" class="mw-redirect">Church Handbook of Instructions</a></i>, Salt Lake City, Utah: LDS Church, p.&#160;85</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aulast=LDS+Church&amp;rft.au=LDS+Church&amp;rft.btitle=Church+Handbook+of+Instructions&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=85&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. Thus, there is a common view within the LDS Church that though prohibited by the LDS Church in mortality, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plural_marriage" title="Plural marriage" class="mw-redirect">plural marriage</a> will exist in the afterlife. See, e.g., <span id="CITEREFPenrose1897" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_W._Penrose" title="Charles W. Penrose">Penrose, Charles W.</a> (1897), <i>Mormon Doctrine Plain and Simple, or Leaves from the Tree of Life</i>, Salt Lake City, UT, p.&#160;66</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aufirst=Charles+W.&amp;rft.aulast=Penrose&amp;rft.au=Penrose%2C+Charles+W.&amp;rft.btitle=Mormon+Doctrine+Plain+and+Simple%2C+or+Leaves+from+the+Tree+of+Life&amp;rft.date=1897&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=66&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+UT&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> ("In the case of a man marrying a wife in the everlasting covenant who dies while he continues in the flesh and marries another by the same divine law, each wife will come forth in her order and enter with him into his glory."); <span id="CITEREFSmith" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Fielding_Smith" title="Joseph Fielding Smith">Smith, Joseph Fielding</a> (1954–56), <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_R._McConkie" title="Bruce R. McConkie">McConkie, Bruce R.</a>, ed., <i>Doctrines of Salvation: Sermons and Writings of Joseph Fielding Smith</i> <b>2</b>, Bookcraft, p.&#160;2</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph+Fielding&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+Joseph+Fielding&amp;rft.btitle=Doctrines+of+Salvation%3A+Sermons+and+Writings+of+Joseph+Fielding+Smith&amp;rft.date=1954%E2%80%9356&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=2&amp;rft.pub=Bookcraft&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.volume=2" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> <span style="display:none;font-size:100%" class="error citation-comment">Check date values in: <code>|date=</code> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:CS1_errors#bad_date" title="Help:CS1 errors">help</a>)</span> (stating of his deceased wives: "my wives will be mine forever").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-79"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-79">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See <span id="CITEREFHyer1992" class="citation">Hyer, Paul V. (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,4177">"Sealing: Temple Sealings"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Mcmillan, p.&#160;12891290, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+V.&amp;rft.au=Hyer%2C+Paul+V.&amp;rft.aulast=Hyer&amp;rft.btitle=Sealing%3A+Temple+Sealings&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C4177&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=12891290&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Mcmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>; <span id="CITEREFThomas1992" class="citation">Thomas, Ryan L. (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,5451">"Adoption of Children"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Mcmillan, pp.&#160;20–21, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.aufirst=Ryan+L.&amp;rft.aulast=Thomas&amp;rft.au=Thomas%2C+Ryan+L.&amp;rft.btitle=Adoption+of+Children&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C5451&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=20%E2%80%9321&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Mcmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. Children born to biological parents who have been sealed to each other are considered "born in the covenant" and need not be sealed to their parents. See <span id="CITEREFCottrell1992" class="citation">Cottrell, Ralph L. (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,5557">"Born in the Covenant"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Macmillan, p.&#160;218, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.au=Cottrell%2C+Ralph+L.&amp;rft.aufirst=Ralph+L.&amp;rft.aulast=Cottrell&amp;rft.btitle=Born+in+the+Covenant&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C5557&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=218&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-wordofwisdom-80"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-wordofwisdom_80-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wordofwisdom_80-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-wordofwisdom_80-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/89">89</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-tithe-81"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tithe_81-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tithing" title="Tithing">Tithing</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.lds.org/topics/tithing?lang=eng">[1]</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-fastoffering-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-fastoffering_82-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Fast_Offerings&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Fast Offerings (page does not exist)">Fast Offerings</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.lds.org/topics/fasting-and-fast-offerings?lang=eng">[2]</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-83"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-83">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_S._Monson" title="Thomas S. Monson">Monson, Thomas S.</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.lds.org/general-conference/2012/10/welcome-to-conference?lang=eng&amp;media=video">"Welcome to Conference"</a>. "We affirm that missionary work is a priesthood duty—and we encourage all young men who are worthy and who are physically able and mentally capable to respond to the call to serve. Many young women also serve, but they are not under the same mandate to serve as are the young men. We assure the young sisters of the Church, however, that they make a valuable contribution as missionaries, and we welcome their service."</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aufirst=Thomas+S.&amp;rft.aulast=Monson&amp;rft.au=Monson%2C+Thomas+S.&amp;rft.btitle=Welcome+to+Conference&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lds.org%2Fgeneral-conference%2F2012%2F10%2Fwelcome-to-conference%3Flang%3Deng%26media%3Dvideo&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-84"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-84">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation journal"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Kimball, Spencer W.</a> (May 1974). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lds.org/ensign/1974/05/planning-for-a-full-and-abundant-life">"Planning for a Full and Abundant Life"</a>. <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ensign_(LDS_magazine)" title="Ensign (LDS magazine)">Ensign</a></i>: 86.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Planning+for+a+Full+and+Abundant+Life&amp;rft.aufirst=Spencer+W.&amp;rft.au=Kimball%2C+Spencer+W.&amp;rft.aulast=Kimball&amp;rft.date=May+1974&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Flds.org%2Fensign%2F1974%2F05%2Fplanning-for-a-full-and-abundant-life&amp;rft.jtitle=Ensign&amp;rft.pages=86&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. This emphasis has been reiterated many times since by various LDS Church leaders.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-ensign200211-85"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-ensign200211_85-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Upon you bishops and you stake presidents rests the responsibility to recommend only those young men and women whom you judge to be spiritually, physically, mentally, and emotionally prepared to face today’s realities of missionary work. Brethren, judge wisely and remember: not every young man needs to be called to serve away from his home; some may best serve under your direction as ward missionaries." <span class="citation journal"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M._Russell_Ballard" title="M. Russell Ballard">Ballard, M. Russell</a> (November 2002). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lds.org/ensign/2002/11/the-greatest-generation-of-missionaries?lang=eng">"The Greatest Generation of Missionaries"</a>. <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ensign_(LDS_magazine)" title="Ensign (LDS magazine)">Ensign</a></i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved March 21, 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=The+Greatest+Generation+of+Missionaries&amp;rft.au=Ballard%2C+M.+Russell&amp;rft.aufirst=M.+Russell&amp;rft.aulast=Ballard&amp;rft.date=November+2002&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.lds.org%2Fensign%2F2002%2F11%2Fthe-greatest-generation-of-missionaries%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rft.jtitle=Ensign&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-86"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-86">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFJoseph_Walker2012" class="citation">Joseph Walker (October 6, 2012), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.deseretnews.com/article/765609643/LDS-Church-lowers-age-requirement-for-missionary-service.html">"LDS Church lowers age requirement for missionary service"</a>, <i>Deseret News</i></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=LDS+Church+lowers+age+requirement+for+missionary+service&amp;rft.au=Joseph+Walker&amp;rft.aulast=Joseph+Walker&amp;rft.date=October+6%2C+2012&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.deseretnews.com%2Farticle%2F765609643%2FLDS-Church-lowers-age-requirement-for-missionary-service.html&amp;rft.jtitle=Deseret+News&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
