<li id="cite_note-89"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-89">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Adherents believe in the Bible "as far as it is translated correctly" See <span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.8?lang=eng#7">Articles of Faith 1:8</a></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-90"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-90">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="plainlinks"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/a-of-f/1.6?lang=eng#5">Articles of Faith 1:6</a></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-91"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-91">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Book of Mormon, Alma 34:8–16.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-92"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-92">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web">Fr. Luis Ladaria, S.J. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ewtn.com/library/theology/mormbap1.htm">"The Question of the Validity of Baptism Conferred in the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints"</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved November 1, 2010</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.au=Fr.+Luis+Ladaria%2C+S.J.&amp;rft.aulast=Fr.+Luis+Ladaria%2C+S.J.&amp;rft.btitle=The+Question+of+the+Validity+of+Baptism+Conferred+in+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-Day+Saints&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ewtn.com%2Flibrary%2Ftheology%2Fmormbap1.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-93"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-93">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mormon.org/restoration">"The Restoration of The Gospel in the Latter Days"</a>. The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved July 13, 2012</span>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=The+Restoration+of+The+Gospel+in+the+Latter+Days&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fmormon.org%2Frestoration&amp;rft.pub=The+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-94"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-94">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">For example, a 2007 poll conducted by the Pew Research Center found that 31 percent of Americans surveyed do not consider Mormons to be Christian. See <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://pewforum.org/surveys/religionviews07/">Public Expresses Mixed Views of Islam, Mormonism</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-95"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-95">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFSmith1842a" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Smith,_Jr." title="Joseph Smith, Jr." class="mw-redirect">Smith, Joseph, Jr.</a> (March 1, 1842), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.centerplace.org/history/ts/v3n09.htm#706">"Church History [Wentworth Letter]"</a>, <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Times_and_Seasons" title="Times and Seasons">Times and Seasons</a></i> <b>3</b> (9): 706–10 [707]</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Church+History+%5BWentworth+Letter%5D&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.date=March+1%2C+1842&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.centerplace.org%2Fhistory%2Fts%2Fv3n09.htm%23706&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.jtitle=Times+and+Seasons&amp;rft.pages=706%E2%80%9310+%5B707%5D&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=3" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (traditional Christian denominations "were believing in incorrect doctrines, and that none of them was acknowledged of God as His church and kingdom"). <span id="CITEREFSmith1842c" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Smith,_Jr." title="Joseph Smith, Jr." class="mw-redirect">Smith, Joseph, Jr.</a> (April 1, 1842), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.centerplace.org/history/ts/v3n11.htm#748">"History of Joseph Smith"</a>, <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Times_and_Seasons" title="Times and Seasons">Times and Seasons</a></i> <b>3</b> (11): 748–49</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=History+of+Joseph+Smith&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.date=April+1%2C+1842&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.centerplace.org%2Fhistory%2Fts%2Fv3n11.htm%23748&amp;rft.issue=11&amp;rft.jtitle=Times+and+Seasons&amp;rft.pages=748%E2%80%9349&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=3" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> Stating that Jesus told Smith that all existing Christian creeds "were an abomination in his sight".</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-96"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-96">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">D&amp;C 1:30 (LDS Church is the "only true and living church upon the face of the whole earth").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-97"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-97">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Spencer_W._Kimball" title="Spencer W. Kimball">Spencer W. Kimball</a>, "<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.lds.org/ensign/1978/11/an-eternal-hope-in-christ">An Eternal Hope in Christ</a>", <i>Ensign</i>, November 1978, p. 71 ("Then he taught and testified that even as Christ is risen from the dead, so will all men come forth from the grave; each will then be judged according to his works, and each will receive his appointed place in the mansions which are prepared. In that resurrected state, Paul said, there are "celestial bodies, and bodies terrestrial, and bodies telestial; but the glory of the celestial, one; and the terrestrial, another; and the telestial, another" (JST, 1 Cor. 15:40)).</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-98"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-98">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFCarter1992" class="citation">Carter, K. Codell (1992), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://contentdm.lib.byu.edu/u?/EoM,3734">"Godhood"</a>, in Ludlow, Daniel H., <i>Encyclopedia of Mormonism</i>, New York: Macmillan, pp.&#160;553–55, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number.html" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X" title="Special:BookSources/0-02-904040-X">0-02-904040-X</a></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Encyclopedia+of+Mormonism&amp;rft.au=Carter%2C+K.+Codell&amp;rft.aufirst=K.+Codell&amp;rft.aulast=Carter&amp;rft.btitle=Godhood&amp;rft.date=1992&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontentdm.lib.byu.edu%2Fu%3F%2FEoM%2C3734&amp;rft.isbn=0-02-904040-X&amp;rft.pages=553%E2%80%9355&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=Macmillan&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> ("The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints teaches that all resurrected and perfected mortals become gods.").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-99"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-99">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">See, for example, <span id="CITEREF" class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.pcusa.org/interfaith/study/lds.htm"><i>Presbyterians and Latter-day Saints</i></a><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved January 30, 2007</span></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=Presbyterians+and+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.pcusa.org%2Finterfaith%2Fstudy%2Flds.htm&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Presbyterian_Church_USA" title="Presbyterian Church USA" class="mw-redirect">Presbyterian Church USA</a>, stating that "Mormonism is a new and emerging religious tradition distinct from the historic apostolic tradition of the Christian Church"); <span id="CITEREF" class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.elca.org/dcm/worship/faq/baptism/rebaptize.html"><i>Should Lutherans Rebaptize Former Mormons Who Are Joining the Congregation?</i></a><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved August 15, 2006</span></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=Should+Lutherans+Rebaptize+Former+Mormons+Who+Are+Joining+the+Congregation%3F&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.elca.org%2Fdcm%2Fworship%2Ffaq%2Fbaptism%2Frebaptize.html&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evangelical_Lutheran_Church_in_America" title="Evangelical Lutheran Church in America">Evangelical Lutheran Church in America</a>, stating that LDS Church doctrine regarding the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trinity" title="Trinity">Trinity</a> is "substantially different from that of orthodox, creedal Christianity"; <span id="CITEREF" class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.gc2000.org/pets/cal/TEXT/c0806.asp"><i>General Conference 2000 806-NonDis</i></a><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved August 15, 2006</span></span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=General+Conference+2000+806-NonDis&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gc2000.org%2Fpets%2Fcal%2FTEXT%2Fc0806.asp&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_Methodist_Church" title="United Methodist Church">United Methodist Church</a>, stating that the LDS Church, "by self-definition, does not fit within the bounds of the historic, apostolic tradition of Christian faith").</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-100"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-100">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">According to <a href="Joseph_Smith.html" title="Joseph Smith">Joseph Smith</a>, Jesus told him that the other churches claiming to be Christian creeds "were an abomination in the Lords sight; that those professors [of religion] were all corrupt". <i>Pearl of Great Price</i>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Smith—History" title="Joseph Smith—History" class="mw-redirect">Joseph Smith—History</a> 1:19.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-101"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-101">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFRoberts1905" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brigham_Henry_Roberts" title="Brigham Henry Roberts" class="mw-redirect">Roberts, B. H</a> (1905), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://books.google.com/?id=m2bEVgSvbS8C"><i>History of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints</i></a> <b>3</b>, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deseret_News" title="Deseret News">Deseret News</a>, pp.&#160;23, 24</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.aufirst=B.+H&amp;rft.aulast=Roberts&amp;rft.au=Roberts%2C+B.+H&amp;rft.btitle=History+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-Day+Saints&amp;rft.date=1905&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2F%3Fid%3Dm2bEVgSvbS8C&amp;rft.pages=23%2C+24&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+News&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.volume=3" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-102"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-102">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFSmithWilliamsCowdery1834" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Smith,_Jr." title="Joseph Smith, Jr." class="mw-redirect">Smith, Joseph, Jr.</a>; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederick_G._Williams" title="Frederick G. Williams">Williams, Frederick G.</a>; <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oliver_Cowdery" title="Oliver Cowdery">Cowdery, Oliver</a> (1834), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.centerplace.org/history/ems/v2n20.htm#160">"Minutes of a Conference of the Elders of the Church of Christ, May 3, 1834"</a>, <i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Evening_and_the_Morning_Star" title="The Evening and the Morning Star">The Evening and the Morning Star</a></i> <b>2</b> (20): 160</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Minutes+of+a+Conference+of+the+Elders+of+the+Church+of+Christ%2C+May+3%2C+1834&amp;rft.au=Cowdery%2C+Oliver&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+Joseph%2C+Jr.&amp;rft.au=Williams%2C+Frederick+G.&amp;rft.date=1834&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.centerplace.org%2Fhistory%2Fems%2Fv2n20.htm%23160&amp;rft.issue=20&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Evening+and+the+Morning+Star&amp;rft.pages=160&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=2" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-103"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-103">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span id="CITEREFSmith1838" class="citation"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Smith,_Jr" title="Joseph Smith, Jr" class="mw-redirect">Smith, Joseph, Jr</a> (August 1838), <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.solomonspalding.com/docs/eldjur04.htm">"Special Collections"</a>, <i>Elders' Journal of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter Day Saints</i> <b>1</b> (4): 52.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.atitle=Special+Collections&amp;rft.aufirst=Joseph%2C+Jr&amp;rft.aulast=Smith&amp;rft.au=Smith%2C+Joseph%2C+Jr&amp;rft.date=August+1838&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.solomonspalding.com%2Fdocs%2Feldjur04.htm&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.jtitle=Elders%27+Journal+of+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter+Day+Saints&amp;rft.pages=52&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.volume=1" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>, <span id="CITEREF1838" class="citation"><i>Manuscript History of the Church, book A-1</i>, LDS Church Archives, 1838, p.&#160;37</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=Manuscript+History+of+the+Church%2C+book+A-1&amp;rft.date=1838&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=37&amp;rft.place=LDS+Church+Archives&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>, reproduced in <span id="CITEREFJessee1989" class="citation">Jessee, Dean C., ed. (1989), <i>The Papers of Joseph Smith: Autobiographical and Historical Writings</i> <b>1</b>, Salt Lake City, Utah: Deseret Book, pp.&#160;302–303</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=The+Papers+of+Joseph+Smith%3A+Autobiographical+and+Historical+Writings&amp;rft.date=1989&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=302%E2%80%93303&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Deseret+Book&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.volume=1" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.<span id="CITEREF1994" class="citation"><i>Inventing Mormonism: Tradition and the Historical Record</i>, Salt Lake City, Utah: Signature Books, 1994, p.&#160;160</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=Inventing+Mormonism%3A+Tradition+and+the+Historical+Record&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.pages=160&amp;rft.place=Salt+Lake+City%2C+Utah&amp;rft.pub=Signature+Books&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-104"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-104">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The initial incorporation by the non-existent <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/State_of_Deseret" title="State of Deseret">State of Deseret</a> <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://content.lib.utah.edu/cdm4/document.php?CISOROOT=/uthisstat&amp;CISOPTR=1756&amp;REC=4">"(1851) Laws and Ordinances of the State of Deseret (Utah) Compilation 1851"</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=%281851%29+Laws+and+Ordinances+of+the+State+of+Deseret+%28Utah%29+Compilation+1851&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontent.lib.utah.edu%2Fcdm4%2Fdocument.php%3FCISOROOT%3D%2Futhisstat%26CISOPTR%3D1756%26REC%3D4&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> was not legally valid, but was soon ratified by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Utah_Territory" title="Utah Territory">Utah Territory</a> in 1851 <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://content.lib.utah.edu/cdm4/document.php?CISOROOT=%2Futhisstat&amp;CISOPTR=448&amp;REC=3&amp;CISOBOX=Church+of+jesus+christ+of+latter-day+saints">"(1851) Acts Resolutions and Memorials Passed by the First Annual and Special Sessions of the Legislative Assembly of the Territory of Utah, 1851"</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=%281851%29+Acts+Resolutions+and+Memorials+Passed+by+the+First+Annual+and+Special+Sessions+of+the+Legislative+Assembly+of+the+Territory+of+Utah%2C+1851&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontent.lib.utah.edu%2Fcdm4%2Fdocument.php%3FCISOROOT%3D%252Futhisstat%26CISOPTR%3D448%26REC%3D3%26CISOBOX%3DChurch%2Bof%2Bjesus%2Bchrist%2Bof%2Blatter-day%2Bsaints&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span> and 1855. See <i>Late Corporation of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-Day Saints v. Romney</i>, 136 U.S. 44–45 (1890).</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-105"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-105">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://content.lib.utah.edu/cdm4/document.php?CISOROOT=/uthisstat&amp;CISOPTR=1756&amp;REC=4">"State of Deseret: An Ordinance, incorporating the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints"</a>. February 4, 1851.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=State+of+Deseret%3A+An+Ordinance%2C+incorporating+the+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.date=February+4%2C+1851&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcontent.lib.utah.edu%2Fcdm4%2Fdocument.php%3FCISOROOT%3D%2Futhisstat%26CISOPTR%3D1756%26REC%3D4&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-106"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-106">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Associated_Press" title="Associated Press">Associated Press</a> continues to says that "Mormon Church" is a proper second reference in its <i>Style Guide</i> for journalists. <span class="citation web"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.westminster-mo.edu/academics/resources/library/resources/Pages/GuidetoAPStyle.aspx">"?"</a>.</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=%3F&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.westminster-mo.edu%2Facademics%2Fresources%2Flibrary%2Fresources%2FPages%2FGuidetoAPStyle.aspx&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span><sup class="noprint Inline-Template"><span style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot" title="Wikipedia:Link rot"><span title="&#160;since October 2010">dead link</span></a></i>]</span></sup></span></li>
