<li id="cite_note-120"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-120">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Relief_Society" title="Relief Society">Relief Society</a> was founded in 1842 in <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nauvoo,_Illinois" title="Nauvoo, Illinois">Nauvoo, Illinois</a>, and with the motto "Charity Never Faileth", the organization today includes more than 5 million women in more than 165 countries. <span id="CITEREF" class="citation"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lds.org/newsroom/showpackage/0,15367,3899-1--43-2-125,00.html"><i>From Pioneer Group to Worldwide Society</i></a>, newsroom.lds.org</span><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AThe+Church+of+Jesus+Christ+of+Latter-day+Saints&amp;rft.btitle=From+Pioneer+Group+to+Worldwide+Society&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Flds.org%2Fnewsroom%2Fshowpackage%2F0%2C15367%2C3899-1--43-2-125%2C00.html&amp;rft.pub=newsroom.lds.org&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>. Every Latter-day Saint woman age 18 or older is a member of the Relief Society.</span></li>
